<TITLE> Govt allows Sheikh Selim to see deceased mother </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, June 28 (bdnews24.com)The government has decided to release Awami League presidium member Sheikh Fazlul Karim Selim on parole, allowing him to see his deceased mother, an official said Thursday. His mother, Achhiya Khatun, 90, the elder sister of independence leader Sheikh Mujibur Rahman, died of old-age complications Thursday at ZH Sikder Medical College Hospital in Gulshan. "The government has decided to release Sheikh Selim on parole from jail, letting him see his mother for the last time," home secretary Abdul Karim told bdnews24.com. Selim's wife sent a letter to the home secretary asking him to allow her husband to see his mother for the last time. bdnews2
